voice_pl1:
"Sometimes I have thought I heard people say my name...Like in a store when you walk past some people you don’t know...But I know they didn’t really say my name so I just go on."

Has something like this ever happened to you?
voice_pl2:
"Sometimes when I am just about to fall asleep, I hear my name as if spoken aloud."

Has something like this ever happened to you?
voice_pl3:
"When I wake up in the morning...But stay in bed for a few minutes, sometimes I hear my mother’s voice...When she’s not there. Like now when I’m living in the dorm. What I hear is her voice saying stuff like, ‘Now come on and get up’ or ‘Don’t be late for school.’ I’m used to it and it doesn’t bother me."

Has something like this ever happened to you?
voice_pl4a:
"I hear a voice that is hard to understand...Can't really tell what it says...Sometimes just as I go to sleep."

Has something like this ever happened to you?
voice_pl4b: Have you had any experience with hearing something just when going to sleep or waking up?
voice_pl5:
"When I was little, I had an imaginary playmate. I remember that I really thought I heard her voice when we talked. That went away...Hearing her voice…but for a while it was just like a real voice."

Has something like this ever happened to you?
voice_pl7:
"Sometimes when I’m in the house all alone, I hear a voice call my name...No, it really isn’t scary. It was at first, but not now...It’s just once...Like ‘Sally’...Kind of quick and like somebody’s calling me. I guess I kind of know that it isn’t really somebody and it’s really me...But it does sound like a real voice."

Has something like this ever happened to you?
voice_pl8:
"Last summer I was hanging up clothes in the backyard. Suddenly I heard my husband call my name from inside the house. He sounded like something was wrong and was loud and clear. I ran in...But he was out in the garage and he hadn’t called at all. Obviously I guess I made it up...But it sounded like a real voice and it was my husband’s."

Has something like this ever happened to you?
voice_pl9:
"I've heard the phone ring or buzz when it didn't."

Has something like this ever happened to you?
voice_pl10:
"I hear my thoughts aloud."

Has something like this ever happened to you?
voice_pl11:
"I have heard God's voice...Not that he made me know in my heart, but as a real voice."

Has something like this ever happened to you?
voice_pl12:
"When I am driving in my car...Particularly when I’m tired or worried...I hear my own voice from the backseat. It’s behind me over my right shoulder. I know it’s really coming from my head, but it sounds like it’s little short statements...Usually soothing...Like ‘It’ll be alright’ or ‘Now, just calm down.'"

Has something like this ever happened to you?
voice_pl13:
"I drive a lot at night. My job has a lot of travel to it. Sometimes late at night, when I’m tired, I hear sounds in the backseat like people talking…But I can’t tell what they say…just a word here and there. When this first started happening...When I first started driving at night so much...Four or five years ago…it scared the hell out of me. But now I’m used to it. I think I do it because I’m tired and by myself."

Has something like this ever happened to you?
voice_pl14:
"Almost every morning while I do my housework, I have a pleasant conversation with my dead grandmother. I talk to her and quite regularly hear her voice actually out loud."

Has something like this ever happened to you?
